### Health Check
GET http://localhost:3001/health

### Register a new student
POST http://localhost:3001/api/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "John Doe",
  "email": "john@example.com",
  "password": "password123",
  "role": "student"
}

### Register an instructor
POST http://localhost:3001/api/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Dr. Smith",
  "email": "smith@example.com",
  "password": "password123",
  "role": "instructor"
}

### Register an admin
POST http://localhost:3001/api/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Admin User",
  "email": "admin@example.com",
  "password": "password123",
  "role": "admin"
}

### Login with student credentials
POST http://localhost:3001/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "john@example.com",
  "password": "password123"
}

### Save token from login response
@studentToken = {{login.response.body.token}}

### Get current user profile (protected)
GET http://localhost:3001/api/auth/me
Authorization: Bearer {{studentToken}}

### Test user dashboard (protected)
GET http://localhost:3001/api/user/dashboard
Authorization: Bearer {{studentToken}}

### Test admin stats (should fail for student)
GET http://localhost:3001/api/admin/stats
Authorization: Bearer {{studentToken}}

### Login with admin credentials
POST http://localhost:3001/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "admin@example.com",
  "password": "password123"
}

### Save admin token
@adminToken = {{login.response.body.token}}

### Test admin stats (should succeed)
GET http://localhost:3001/api/admin/stats
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

### Test invalid login
POST http://localhost:3001/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "nonexistent@example.com",
  "password": "wrongpassword"
}

### Test validation errors (short password)
POST http://localhost:3001/api/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Test",
  "email": "invalid-email",
  "password": "123"
}